<subsection xml:id="subsec-length-of-an-arc-of-a-circle-1">
    <title>length of an arc of a circle 1</title>
    <statement>
      <p>
        In the previous section we have explored about getting (perimeter) the circumference of a circle. Can you remember how you did it?
      </p>
      <p>
        In this section we will calculate the arc length of two sectors namely,semi-circle and quarter circle.
      </p>
      <p>
       An arc is a part of the circumference of a circle.
      </p>
      <sidebyside>
      <image>
            <latex-image label = "circle-4">
              \begin{tikzpicture}
                \fill[blue] (-2,0) arc[start angle=180, end angle=360, radius=2cm] -- (0,0) -- cycle;
                % Draw the radius and label it 'r'
                \draw[thick, -&gt;] (0,0) -- (2,0) node[midway, above] {\large $r = 21 cm$};
                % Draw the center point
                \fill (0,0) circle (2pt);
                \node at (-1,0){Semi-circle};
              \end{tikzpicture}
            </latex-image>
            </image>
            <image>
            <latex-image label = "threequarter">
              begin{tikzpicture}
                % Draw a 3/4 (270-degree) filled green circle
                \fill[green] (0,0) -- (2,0) arc[start angle=0, end angle=270, radius=2cm] -- cycle;
                
                % Draw the outline of the 3/4 circle
                \draw[thick] (2,0) arc[start angle=0, end angle=270, radius=2cm] -- (0,0) -- cycle;
                
                % Indicate the radius with a label 'r'
                \draw[thick, -&gt;] (0,0) -- (2,0) node[midway, above] {\large $ = 7 cm$};
                
                % Draw the center point
                \fill (0,0) circle (2pt);
              \end{tikzpicture}
            </latex-image>
            </image>
       </sidebyside>
      </statement>
      <exploration>
        <statement>
           <p>Find the circumference of a semi-circle with a diameter of <m>10.5\text{ cm }</m>.  Use <m>\pi = \frac{22}{7}</m></p>
          <sidebyside>
           <image width = "50%">
            <latex-image label="semi-circle">
              \begin{tikzpicture}
                % Draw the semicircle
                \draw [very thick,fill=white](3.5,0) arc [start angle=0, end angle=180, radius=3.5cm];
                % Draw the diameter
                \draw [thick , fill=pink](-3.5,0) -- (3.5,0);
                \node at(0, -0.5) {\huge{d = 10.5 cm}};
              \end{tikzpicture}
            </latex-image >
           </image>
                <p>
              <md>
                <mrow> \text{ Circumference } = \amp \frac{1}{2}\pi d + d</mrow>
                <mrow>  = \amp \frac {22}{7} \times 10.5 \text{ cm } + 10.5 \text { cm } </mrow>
                <mrow>  = \amp \frac {22 \times 10.5}{14} \text{ cm } + 10.5 \text { cm } </mrow>
                <mrow>  = \amp 16.5\text{ cm } + 10.5 \text { cm }</mrow>
                <mrow> = \amp 27 \text{ cm }</mrow>
              </md>
              </p>
          </sidebyside>
        </statement>
      </exploration>


          <p>
            Find the perimeter of the figure below.
          </p>
        <image>
          <latex-image label = "circle-2">
            \begin{tikzpicture}
              \fill[pink] (-2,0) arc[start angle=180, end angle=360, radius=2cm] -- (0,0) -- cycle;
              % Draw the radius and label it 'r'
              \draw[thick, -&gt;] (0,0) -- (2,0) node[midway, above] {\large $r = 21 cm$};
              % Draw the center point
              \fill (0,0) circle (2pt);
            \end{tikzpicture}
          </latex-image>
          </image>
      
  </subsection>
  